# Cursor Rules — Nóos Platform

## MANDATORY: Read BUSINESS_LOGIC.md first

Before making any change, read `BUSINESS_LOGIC.md` in the repo root.
It covers: roles, permissions, auth flow, patient ownership, evaluation flow,
test types, NEURONORMA scoring, frontend routes, security rules, data models.
Update it in the same commit whenever you change business logic, rules, or data models.

## Key rules

- Schema changes: Alembic migrations only — never `Base.metadata.create_all()` in app code
- Every mutating route: call `audit()` before `db.commit()`
- Every patient route: call `can_access_patient()` — see `app/api/utils/access.py`
- Frontend errors: always use `extractApiError()` from `@/utils/apiError`
- Role strings are Spanish: `"Administrador"` / `"Neuropsicólogo"` / `"Observador"`
- Patients are anonymous (GDPR): no names, DNI, email, phone — only age/education/laterality
- Business logic belongs in `app/services/`, not in route handlers
- Rate limiting required on auth endpoints via `@limiter.limit()`

## Full architecture

See `.github/copilot-instructions.md` and `AGENTS.md` for complete patterns,
non-negotiables, security model, and known technical debt.
